						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the central shrine in the Vālīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, engraved in characters of the 12th century is damaged at the beginning and hence the king's name and the regnal year are lost.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of 64 cows, by Niṉṟaiyūr-nāṭṭāṉ of Naḍuviṉ-malai, for burning two perpetual lamps in the temple. The measure called <hi rend="italic">tirukkārikaraiyuḍaiyāṉ</hi> is also mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
